{"title_page": "Pissy Pamper", "text_new": "{{Short description|Unreleased demo by Young Nudy and Pi'erre Bourne featuring Playboi Carti}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Pissy Pamper (Kid Cudi)\n| type          = song\n| released      = April 18, 2019 (leak)\n| artist        = [[Young Nudy]] and [[Pi'erre Bourne]] featuring [[Playboi Carti]]\n| genre         = Hip Hop & Rap\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=21}}\n| label         = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[Young Nudy|Quantavious Thomas]]|[[Pi'erre Bourne|Jordan Jenks]]|[[Playboi Carti|Jordan Carter]]|[[AB'S|Makoto Matsushita]]}}\n| producer      = [[Pi'erre Bourne]]\n| misc          = {{Audio sample\n | type        = song\n | header      = \n | file        = Young Nudy Pierre Bourne Pissy Pamper.ogg\n | description = Audio sample featuring Young Nudy rapping and Playboi Carti's \"baby voice\".\n}}}}\n\"'''Pissy Pamper'''\", popularly referred to as \"'''Kid Cudi'''\", is an unreleased song by American rapper [[Young Nudy]] and American record producer [[Pi'erre Bourne]], featuring American rapper [[Playboi Carti]]. The song initially [[Internet leak|leaked online]] on April 2019. An unofficial upload of the song, featuring just Playboi Carti's verse, topped the [[Spotify]] US Viral 50 chart in late May 2019 after a performance at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]].\n\n==Background==\n\"Pissy Pamper\" was produced by Pi'erre Bourne for ''Sli'merre'', his collaborative album with Young Nudy. The song was not included on the album due to a sample clearance issue. Young Nudy had sent the song to Playboi Carti to record a verse. Upon being sent back the verse, Young Nudy reacted by saying \"Man, what the fuck is Carti talking about? He sound like a goddamn baby.\"<ref name=\"Fader\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/06/27/young-nudy-slimerre-kid-cudi-pissy-pamper-atlanta-interview|title=The FADER Interview with Young Nudy, the people's champ of Atlanta|author=Ben Dandridge Lemco|website=[[The Fader]]|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nPlayboi Carti's verse was first previewed on [[Instagram|Instagram Live]] as a snippet in March 2019, where the song was dubbed \"Kid Cudi\" due to Playboi Carti referencing American rapper [[Kid Cudi]] by name twice: \"Brand new pack like Kid Cudi / I smoke dope like Kid Cudi\". [[Internet meme]]s, usually featuring NBA players of the [[Brooklyn Nets]], using Playboi Carti's verse quickly became popular prior to the song's full leak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/a-leaked-upload-of-playboi-cartis-kid-cudi-is-currently-no1-on-spotifys-us-viral-50-chart-news.80875.html|title=A Leaked Upload Of Playboi Carti's \"Kid Cudi\" Is Currently No.1 On Spotify's US Viral 50 Chart|author=Nada Mesh|date=21 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=HotNewHipHop}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nThe song is built upon a sample of Japanese singer [[Mai Yamane]]'s 1980 song \"Tasogare\".<ref name=\"Genius\">{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/playboi-carti-scores-a-viral-hit-with-kid-cudi-a-leaked-snippet-from-a-song-that-s-not-even-his-aka-pissy-pamper|title=Playboi Carti Scores A Viral Hit With \u201cKid Cudi,\u201d A Leaked Snippet From A Song That\u2019s Not Even His|date=3 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|author=Chris Mench}}</ref> Playboi Carti uses his viral \"baby voice Carti\" technique for his guest feature, with his voice hitting a high pitch with unclear pronunciations and frantic cadences.<ref name=\"Baby\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/05/playboi-carti-baby-voice-history/|title=The History of Playboi Carti's Baby Voice|date=10 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|author=Greg Gaffney|website=Complex}}</ref>\n\n==Leak and success==\n[[File:Playboi_Carti.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Playboi Carti]]'s use of his high pitch \"baby voice\" allowed an unofficial upload of just his verse top the [[Spotify]] US Viral 50 chart in May 2019]]\nThe entire song was leaked on April 18, 2019, revealed to be a [[Young Nudy]] and [[Pi'erre Bourne]] track titled \"Pissy Pamper\". The song wasn't included on the collaborative album ''Sli'merre'' due to [[Sampling (music)|sample]] clearance issues.<ref name=\"Interview\"/> The song became popular due to the \"baby voice Carti\" verse, a voice technique previously used by Carti on American singer [[Solange Knowles|Solange]]'s \"[[Almeda (song)|Almeda]]\", and was boosted by [[Internet meme]]s.<ref name=\"Baby\"/><ref name=\"Billboard\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8512748/playboi-carti-kid-cudi-spotify-charts|title=Fan Sneaks Unreleased Playboi Carti Song to DSPs, Tops Spotify's US Viral 50 Chart|author=Carl Lamarre|date=22 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|work=Billboard}}</ref>\n\nA high school sophomore under the name Lil Kambo uploaded Carti's verse to [[Spotify]] under the title \"Kid Carti\". In an interview with [[Genius (website)|Genius]], Kambo explained \"I first made my Spotify account to post songs that aren\u2019t already on Spotify. Before the song came out there was a snippet on YouTube and it sounded like it would be a hit if it was released. A couple weeks later the song got leaked and I posted it to my channel not thinking about how big it would get.\"<ref name=\"Kambo\">{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/an-unofficial-upload-of-playboi-carti-s-kid-cudi-is-no-1-on-spotify-s-us-viral-50-chart|title=An Unofficial Upload Of Playboi Carti's 'Kid Cudi' Is No. 1 On Spotify's US Viral 50 Chart|date=21 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=Genius|author=Chris Mench}}</ref> After Kambo shared the link to his upload on [[Reddit]], along with Carti's performance of his verse during his set at the 2019 [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]], the unofficial upload topped the US Viral 50 chart on May 20, 2019 with over two million streams.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/05/21/playboi-carti-pissy-pamper-kid-cudi-spotify-viral|title=A clip of Playboi Carti\u2019s leaked song \"Kid Cudi\" is number one on the Spotify Viral 50 Chart|author=Jordan Darville|date=21 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=The Fader}}</ref> The song was removed from Spotify on May 22, 2019.<ref name=\"Kambo\"/> By June 26, 2019, another unofficial upload of Playboi Carti's verse, under the title \"Kid Cudi Only Carti\", by YungGen, had climbed up into the top 5 of the Spotify Viral 50 chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/here-s-the-origin-of-every-leaked-song-on-playboi-carti-s-apple-music-account|title=Multiple Leaked Playboi Carti Tracks Have Appeared Under His Official Apple Music Account|date=26 June 2019|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|author1=Isaac Welch|author2=Chris Mench}}</ref>, but then got taken down. By July 2019, yet another unofficial upload of the full song, by King Zay, had climbed to the Spotify US Viral 50 chart until it got detected. More unofficial uploads of the song continues to be released.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nIn a May 2019 interview with ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'', Young Nudy stated that he did not \"give a damn\" that the song did not make it onto ''Sli'merre''. He added that, \"Sometimes you think you made the best song in the world, and someone come out the blue talking about, 'You can't use that sample.' You just gotta move on.\"<ref name=\"Interview\">{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/levels/young-nudy-interview/|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=30 May 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019|title=Young Nudy Is Putting the Bullshit Behind Him|author=Alphonse Pierre}}</ref> Young Nudy reiterated that he \"ain't give a fuck\" that the song had leaked in a June 2019 interview with ''[[The Fader]]''.<ref name=\"Fader\"/>\n\nSoon Later a \u201cYouTube\u201d Channel called Shayleaks posted the leak on his channel under the name \u201cKid Cudi\u201d it received over 26 million views before it got taken down by \u201cSME\u201d\n\n==Reception==\nOn June 27, 2019, [[Connecticut Public Radio]]'s ''[[Colin McEnroe|The Colin McEnroe Show]]'' named \"Pissy Pamper\" as a contender for 2019 Song of the Summer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wnpr.org/post/2019-song-summer|title=The 2019 Song Of The Summer Is...|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019|publisher=[[Connecticut Public Radio|WNPR]]|author1=Chion Wolf|author2=[[Colin McEnroe]]}}</ref> In a July 2019 article, Douglas Markowitz of the ''[[Phoenix New Times]]'' included \"Pissy Pamper\" on the newspaper's list of \"Favorite Songs of 2019 (So Far)\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/music/favorite-songs-of-2019-so-far-injury-reserve-playboi-carti-vampire-weekend-11315238|title=Phoenix New Times' Favorite Songs of 2019 (So Far)|date=2 July 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019|work=[[Phoenix New Times]]|author=Douglas Markowitz}}</ref> In its year-end list, ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' listed \"Pissy Pamper\" at number 43 on its list of the 100 best songs of 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/best-songs-2019/|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019|accessdate=9 December 2019|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Playboi Carti}}{{Young Nudy}}\n\n[[Category:Songs written by Playboi Carti]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Unreleased songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about cannabis]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Unreleased demo by Young Nudy and Pi'erre Bourne featuring Playboi Carti}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Pissy Pamper\n| type          = song\n| released      = April 18, 2019 (leak)\n| artist        = [[Young Nudy]] and [[Pi'erre Bourne]] featuring [[Playboi Carti]]\n| genre         = <!--do not add unsourced genres-->\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=21}}\n| label         = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[Young Nudy|Quantavious Thomas]]|[[Pi'erre Bourne|Jordan Jenks]]|[[Playboi Carti|Jordan Carter]]|[[AB'S|Makoto Matsushita]]}}\n| producer      = [[Pi'erre Bourne]]\n| misc          = {{Audio sample\n | type        = song\n | header      = \n | file        = Young Nudy Pierre Bourne Pissy Pamper.ogg\n | description = Audio sample featuring Young Nudy rapping and Playboi Carti's \"baby voice\".\n}}}}\n\"'''Pissy Pamper'''\", popularly referred to as \"'''Kid Cudi'''\", is an unreleased song by American rapper [[Young Nudy]] and American record producer [[Pi'erre Bourne]], featuring American rapper [[Playboi Carti]]. The song initially [[Internet leak|leaked online]] on April 2019. An unofficial upload of the song, featuring just Playboi Carti's verse, topped the [[Spotify]] US Viral 50 chart in late May 2019 after a performance at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]].\n\n==Background==\n\"Pissy Pamper\" was produced by Pi'erre Bourne for ''Sli'merre'', his collaborative album with Young Nudy. The song was not included on the album due to a sample clearance issue. Young Nudy had sent the song to Playboi Carti to record a verse. Upon being sent back the verse, Young Nudy reacted by saying \"Man, what the fuck is Carti talking about? He sound like a goddamn baby.\"<ref name=\"Fader\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/06/27/young-nudy-slimerre-kid-cudi-pissy-pamper-atlanta-interview|title=The FADER Interview with Young Nudy, the people's champ of Atlanta|author=Ben Dandridge Lemco|website=[[The Fader]]|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nPlayboi Carti's verse was first previewed on [[Instagram|Instagram Live]] as a snippet in March 2019, where the song was dubbed \"Kid Cudi\" due to Playboi Carti referencing American rapper [[Kid Cudi]] by name twice: \"Brand new pack like Kid Cudi / I smoke dope like Kid Cudi\". [[Internet meme]]s, usually featuring NBA players of the [[Brooklyn Nets]], using Playboi Carti's verse quickly became popular prior to the song's full leak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/a-leaked-upload-of-playboi-cartis-kid-cudi-is-currently-no1-on-spotifys-us-viral-50-chart-news.80875.html|title=A Leaked Upload Of Playboi Carti's \"Kid Cudi\" Is Currently No.1 On Spotify's US Viral 50 Chart|author=Nada Mesh|date=21 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=HotNewHipHop}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nThe song is built upon a sample of Japanese singer [[Mai Yamane]]'s 1980 song \"Tasogare\".<ref name=\"Genius\">{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/playboi-carti-scores-a-viral-hit-with-kid-cudi-a-leaked-snippet-from-a-song-that-s-not-even-his-aka-pissy-pamper|title=Playboi Carti Scores A Viral Hit With \u201cKid Cudi,\u201d A Leaked Snippet From A Song That\u2019s Not Even His|date=3 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|author=Chris Mench}}</ref> Playboi Carti uses his viral \"baby voice Carti\" technique for his guest feature, with his voice hitting a high pitch with unclear pronunciations and frantic cadences.<ref name=\"Baby\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/05/playboi-carti-baby-voice-history/|title=The History of Playboi Carti's Baby Voice|date=10 May 2019|accessdate=25 May 2019|author=Greg Gaffney|website=Complex}}</ref>\n\n==Leak and success==\n[[File:Playboi_Carti.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Playboi Carti]]'s use of his high pitch \"baby voice\" allowed an unofficial upload of just his verse top the [[Spotify]] US Viral 50 chart in May 2019]]\nThe entire song was leaked on April 18, 2019, revealed to be a [[Young Nudy]] and [[Pi'erre Bourne]] track titled \"Pissy Pamper\". The song wasn't included on the collaborative album ''Sli'merre'' due to [[Sampling (music)|sample]] clearance issues.<ref name=\"Interview\"/> The song became popular due to the \"baby voice Carti\" verse, a voice technique previously used by Carti on American singer [[Solange Knowles|Solange]]'s \"[[Almeda (song)|Almeda]]\", and was bo