of the Spotify Viral 50 chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/here-s-the-origin-of-every-leaked-song-on-playboi-carti-s-apple-music-account|title=Multiple Leaked Playboi Carti Tracks Have Appeared Under His Official Apple Music Account|date=26 June 2019|website=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|author1=Isaac Welch|author2=Chris Mench}}</ref>, but then got taken down. By July 2019, yet another unofficial upload of the full song, by King Zay, had climbed to the Spotify US Viral 50 chart until it got detected. More unofficial uploads of the song continues to be released.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nIn a May 2019 interview with ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'', Young Nudy stated that he did not \"give a damn\" that the song did not make it onto ''Sli'merre''. He added that, \"Sometimes you think you made the best song in the world, and someone come out the blue talking about, 'You can't use that sample.' You just gotta move on.\"<ref name=\"Interview\">{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/levels/young-nudy-interview/|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=30 May 2019|accessdate=2 July 2019|title=Young Nudy Is Putting the Bullshit Behind Him|author=Alphonse Pierre}}</ref> Young Nudy reiterated that he \"ain't give a fuck\" that the song had leaked in a June 2019 interview with ''[[The Fader]]''.<ref name=\"Fader\"/>\n\n==Reception==\nOn June 27, 2019, [[Connecticut Public Radio]]'s ''[[Colin McEnroe|The Colin McEnroe Show]]'' named \"Pissy Pamper\" as a contender for 2019 Song of the Summer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wnpr.org/post/2019-song-summer|title=The 2019 Song Of The Summer Is...|date=27 June 2019|accessdate=3 July 2019|publisher=[[Connecticut Public Radio|WNPR]]|author1=Chion Wolf|author2=[[Colin McEnroe]]}}</ref> In a July 2019 article, Douglas Markowitz of the ''[[Phoenix New Times]]'' included \"Pissy Pamper\" on the newspaper's list of \"Favorite Songs of 2019 (So Far)\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/music/